Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a #kettle{} full.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Pop the sliced pepper and @diced butternut squash{300%g} onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, sprinkle over half the @Mexican style spice mix{1%sachet}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled @water{} into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @basmati rice{100%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

While everything cooks, drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a sieve. Put half into a #bowl{} and mash with the back of a #fork{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and remaining Mexican style spice mix to the chorizo. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant.

Once fragrant, stir the @water for the beans{100%ml}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and black beans (whole and crushed) into the garlic.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium and simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

While the beans simmer, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Once the beans are ready, taste and add salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if they're a little too dry.

When ready, fluff up the rice with a fork and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the chorizo, refried beans and roasted veg.

Add a dollop of @soured cream{75%g}, then scatter over the grated cheese.

Enjoy!